This paper deals with the interpretation of classical proofs as interactive learning strategies, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of monads in the presentation of the interpretation suggests a connection to functional programming (cs.PL) and category theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretation of arithmetic, which is a topic that is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
